description:
I plan on getting more time on this target to eventually get a good-looking Squid, but the weather is just not cooperating right now. I wanted to share this image to show the intense Ha region. I just love the depth and structure here. I removed the stars to further enhance the views of the nebulosity. Hope you enjoy.

Gear:
Camera: ASI1600MM w/ EAF, EFW
Filters: Astrodon 5nm HA, 3nm OIII
Scope: Meade Series 6000 70mm f/5 Astrograph Quadruplet
Guidescope: Williams Optics 50mm
Guidecam: ASI120MM mini
Mount: SW EQ6R-Pro
Pegasus Astro Pocket Power Box
Astro-Zap dew heaters

Image details:
25x300s HA, Gain 139, -10c
23x420s OIII, Gain 139, -10c
25 darks, flats, darkflats
5.6 hrs total
Acquisition/Edits:
SharpCap, NINA, PHD2, Stellarium, Pixinsight, Photoshop
title: Sh2-129 Flying Bat Nebula (Starless)(Squidless)
